Energy experts believe Minister Gwede Mantashe’s proposal of clean coal energy generation will do little but cost the sinking energy sector loads of money, while failing to ensure a reduction in emissions of greenhouse gases. Researcher from environment justice lobby group Groundwork, David Hallowes, said Mantashe’s proposal of clean coal energy through carbon stripping initiatives would cost the energy sector millions of wasted rands. “The proposal of clean coal is merely there to justify coal-generated energy. There is no such thing as clean coal mining, and coal is a dirty business. Even the proposed technology of carbon stripping will not...